<typeStatus box="[876,926,2010,2034]" pageId="1" pageNumber="158">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName authority="Reuter, 1891" authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1891" box="[1019,1308,2010,2034]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Mecistoscelis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="158" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scirtetoides">
<emphasis box="[1019,1170,2010,2034]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="158">M. scirtetoides</emphasis>
Reuter, 1891
</taxonomicName>
, monobasic. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,152,179]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Relatively thin and elongate bug (total length ranging between 
<quantity box="[993,1112,152,179]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" unit="mm" value="6.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="5.0">5 to 8 mm</quantity>
, total width approximately 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
). Labium reaching beyond metacoxa (
<bibRefCitation author="Lansbury, I." box="[623,793,189,215]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref7831" refString="Lansbury, I. (1963) Revision of the tribe Mecistoscelini Reuter (Hemiptera-Heteroptera, Miridae). Bulletin of Entomology, 4, 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="1963">Lansbury 1963</bibRefCitation>
<emphasis box="[800,873,190,215]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="159">contra</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Carvalho, J. C. M." box="[879,1048,188,215]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" pagination="1 - 151" refId="ref7090" refString="Carvalho, J. C. M. (1955) Key Genera Miridae of the world. Boletim do Museu Paraense Emilio Goeldi, 11 (2), 1 - 151." type="journal article" year="1955">Carvalho 1955</bibRefCitation>
). Pilosity of two first antennal segments, femora and tibia short. First antennal segment about as long as head, pronotum and scutellum together (Distant 1904, for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1891" box="[312,479,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Mecistoscelis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scirtetoides">
<emphasis box="[312,479,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="159">M. scirtetoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Second antennal segment longer than the first. Third antennal segment the longest. Fourth antennal segment about as long as the second. Ostiolar peritreme yellowish. Cuneus obviously longer than wide at base. Left paramere with long setae subapically on its dorso-outer margin. Body of right paramere narrow, its apex bifid.
</paragraph>
